				</tr>
				<tr>
					<TD vAlign=top width="18%" style="background: #333333;">
						<B>AlDjotte</B><BR> Normal Player						<p>
																							</TD>
					<TD style="background: #333333;" valign=top>
						<IMG src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/posticon.gif" border=0> posted 2005-01-07 06:54&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
 						<A href="edit.php?board=sug&id=1879"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			 			<A href="reply.php?board=sug&id=1879"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A> </FONT>
			  			<HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  			I think the game is great, lots of playing depth and space for strategy...<br />
<br />
There is, however, a serious imbalance with the importance of commie detection: if a player has better commies and equips his fleet with HBH, he can come away from a battle against the best player with 0 casualties with a fleet only 30% larger. Since you can hit players 1/2 your size, that means he can go on a rampage, losing nothing along the way.<br />
<br />
That is not realistic (tho' that matters little), but its really bad for play balance : growing for no loss should only be possible at the expense of silly players.<br />
<br />
I just lost 100-120 dooms with level 20 commies, all with above average stats at the start (tho' targs, so not great) without a single defensive shot being fired to 4 fleets of dooms (so up to 160 dooms). They were all end-tech dooms, in a tight formation : ie nothing stupid. It's just crazy that you can get owned like that :-(<br />
<br />
Here's what I suggest:<br />
i) Doubling the range that commies can see, so most level 20 commies can see further than they can fire<br />
ii) Adding an initiative roll to decide who goes first if two fleets move into range when they can both see each other : say d10+Initiative Commie skill (say replace the unused interpretation skill)<br />
iii) nerfing the HBH range to be slightly less than DB/HDRL and similar weapons<br />
<br />
That way commie detection is important at low level to see who fires first (&quot;Oh #@'% there's an enemy ship on top of us&quot;), and to allow ships to see and move towards enemy ships at all levels.<br />
<br />
At higher level, the new initiative commie skill becomes important, but with a big random factor (the fastest gunfighter doesn't always shoot first)<br />
<br />
An HBH armed ship has to close through DB and other fire close enough to launch its' deadly cargo (tweaking other weapon ranges would probably also be worhtwhile)<br />
<br />
OK vets, flame my idea !						<P align=right> </P>
					</TD>
				</TR>
	
		
